sitting all alone
in your room dark and cold
trying to figure out this life
why doesnt it fit
the picture perfect mold

instead you sit there
scars on your wrist
and tears in your eyes
but no one understands (no one understands)
why you need to cry

pre chorus
they dont see
what lays inside
they dont see
all that you hide
they dont know
how you feel
they dont know
life had no appeal

chorus:

nothing to do
sitting here(sitting here)
thinking bout you
so torn up
dont know what to say

parents dont see

they dont belive in you
in your ways
dont believe you can go far

starting to believe

not worth living you life

Lord forgive me
               B.P.H. feb.21,2005
i pray to god day after day
please dont let me fall
dont let me waste away

cause if i were to be gone
would others still belong
in this world
can they last 
and forget 
i was part of the past

lord can you forgive me
for what ive done
im sorry i didnt like this life
sorry i wasnt having fun
now you look at me 
knocking on your door
these words you told me
"your not wecome in heaven anymore"

"i can not forgive
for the crime you committed
you quite the life
i gave you to live
wish you would have admitted
that you were wrong 
in believeing 
that in this world you dont belong"

i look upon the ground
and shead a tear
why didnt i live for the ones
i hold so dear
i didnt give them the chance
to help me through
i gave up on them
and i gave up on you

the tears still flow
as  i turn around
and say to hell i go
a voice called out "wait"
and someone opened 
the pearly gate

you are welcome now
you figured out how
you went wrong 
and that anywhere 
you can belong
i hold out my hand 
to help you 
to fully understand
that people care for you

the voice       Feb 1,2005
                     B.P.H.
theres this voice, he lives in my head
 he speaks of dreadful things
and hurtful words are said
almost like a whisper in my ear
he tells me," i want you dead"

painful words
and no tears to cry
 sometimes i think
"maybe ill let him win
maybe ill just die"

hes mad at me, dont know why
the visions he sends
make me cry
i dont want to fight him anymore
i dont want to try

hes controling
but he cant control me
i'll break away from him
and soon, from "the voice", 
i'll be free

the rain drizzles down
on this child all alone
sitting by herself
on the riverbanks
made of stone

the water rages by
as a lonely tear falls
to join the flow
sitting here thinking to herself
bout the pain
no one will ever know

her head is spinning
she is so confused
thinking if everyone is real
if they really cared
or was she just being used

 

this land has perished
dried out by the sun
the  rain no longer falls
and destruction is all but done

this world has been torn
into the pieces of two
it shall now crumble and fall
upon both me and you

this heart has been wounded
by the words you told
there seems to be nothing left
no one for me to hold

i wanna write so much
 dont know what to fuckin'say
ill be messed up 
to the end of my day
screw this life 
screw this world
screw this knife
let  hate be unfurled
im breaking you apart 
slam you to the ground
rip out you heart 
where love was once bound
ill take you down
to hell with me
burn you with flames
then youll see
how pissed off you made me
mess you up with the Pcp
i will fight you to the end of my day
wont give it up
till i have my fucking way
ill beat you down
kick your ass
straight outta town

you see me laying there
yet you do nothing,
you look down upon me
without a care
for what had happened.
now i know,
not to get you mad
cause something  always goes
unbelieveably bad.
something had gone wrong
something horribly twisted
for me,now, your feelings
had suddenly shifted.
it seems im always the one,
whose heart has to be broken
and with this life
i believe i am done.
there is nothing more,
there is nothing left,
and in my heart,
remains a painful cleft.

 

Can't you see? Don't you care
I want to die?
Don't you listen? Can't you hear
My silent cry?

Won't you turn? Can't you hold
Me to your heart?
Are you afraid of what might follow
Once you start?

Would you rather not believe
I'm in such pain
That all your sense and good advice
Must be in vain?

Would you rather tell yourself
I'll be OK,
And all this adolescent angst
Will go away?

Ah! Would I also swim across
This lake alone!
But if you cannot swim with me,
I know I'll drown.

by Nicholas Gordon

If I Died Today

by: Me

if i died today
would you miss me
if i died today
would you go to my grave
to visit me
would you cry a tear
and wish i was still here
would you say a prayer
to keep me there

if i died today
would you laugh at me
if i died today
would you go to my grave
and spit upon me
would say good shes gone
ive wanted her dead all along
would you turn you back and walk away
not even say godbye on that day

Rain

By;Me

blue skies and a sunny day
are ideal for some
but i prefer the rain

watching the rain
splashing gently against the ground
bringing beauty to the world
where,before, it was never found

when the skies are all clouded
and filled with dark gray
i venture out to capture the beauty of the rain

every little drop
is heavens uncried tear
the smell is so pleasant
and the sound is one i like to hear

so when sunny days come around
and im shut in the house,
rememberi prefer the rain

 

Warped & Twisted
by Skittles
Harsh words & violent blows
Hidden secrets nobody knows
Eyes are open, hands are fisted
Deep inside I'm warped & twisted
So many tricks & so many lies
Too many whens & too many whys
Nobody's special, nobody's gifted
I'm just me, warped & twisted
Sleeping awake & choking on a dream
Listening loudly to a silent scream
Call my mind, the number's unlisted
Lost in someone so warped & twisted
On my knees, alive but dead
Look at the invisible blood I've bled
I'm not gone, my mind has drifted
Don't expect much, I'm warped & twisted
Burnt out, wasted, empty, & hollow
Today's just yesterday's tomorrow
The sun died out, the ashes sifted
I'm still here, warped & twisted

dead secrets
lie amonst the dust
mixed with these emotions
and long lost trust
it sings this song
that'll make you go mad
this song
is the anthem of the sad

dead secrets
avoid everlasting stares
hiding their existance
from all who care
it reads you this story
that shall make you cry
this story
is the truth of how you die

walking down the lonely road
where the wind blows cold
and the leaves blow by
as your eyes wander up
and look at the dark peaceful sky

so brilliant are the stars
and bright the moon
they captivate you in such a way
that this cold  dark night
is better than the brightest days

its beauty makes you smile with delight
fills you with a feeling only felt at night
when you walk the road alone
on a beautiful cold night like this
it feels better than a warm night at home

Currently untitled

you see this look in my eyes
past the pain the hate and the lies
it stands alone
there on its own
trying to forgive the past
and make the true happiness last

my eyes i do close
to hide the pain it all shows
to keep it hidden from you
i didnt want you to know the pain, its true
i want to hide it from everyone you see
though i want them to know the real me

this world is so wrong
and no one seems to belong
it doesnt matter our color or race
you can see the sadness plastered upon our face
no one can really see
how twisted another's soul can be
